diagnoses: description: A viral infection that primarily affects teenagers and young adults. It is characterized by fever, fatigue, sore throat, swollen lymph nodes (including cervical lymphadenopathy), and an enlarged spleen.
description: A rare but serious condition caused by bacterial toxins that can affect multiple organ systems. Symptoms include fever, rash, low blood pressure, and shock.

description: An autoimmune disease that can affect many parts of the body, including the skin, joints, kidneys, and brain. Symptoms can vary widely, but may include fever, fatigue, joint pain, rash, and kidney problems.
description: A severe allergic reaction to certain medications that can cause a variety of symptoms, including fever, rash, swollen lymph nodes, and internal organ involvement.
description: A viral infection that is usually mild but can cause serious problems in people with weakened immune systems. Symptoms can include fever, fatigue, swollen lymph nodes, and muscle aches.
description: A rare condition that primarily affects children and causes inflammation of the blood vessels. Symptoms include fever, rash, swollen lymph nodes, and red eyes.
description: A bacterial infection spread by ticks. Symptoms can include fever, headache, fatigue, and a characteristic bulls-eye rash.
description: A complication of untreated strep throat that can cause inflammation of the heart, joints, and other tissues. Symptoms include fever, joint pain, and a skin rash.
description: A serious infection that can lead to shock, organ failure, and death. Symptoms can include fever, chills, rapid breathing, and confusion.
description: A severe and potentially life-threatening skin reaction that can be caused by certain medications. Symptoms include widespread blistering and peeling of the skin.
